	(text "R_{SNS} (R13) selection per datasheet:\n56m, 68m, 100m\nThe higher the value, the lower is charging current."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 102.616 109.474 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "0381b75c-df21-404b-b666-b2d4fb76a512")
	)
	(text "D4 is a TVS disode recommended\nin Awinic's datasheets,\nmaybe it's not needed on practice."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 53.594 75.438 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "15862c30-1a01-4ac2-98bd-3fdda89b2b17")
	)
	(text "3 of 4 charge ICs use internal buck converter to generate output voltage.\nThis requires a suitable inductor. I_{sat} of selected indutor has to be bigger than\npeak current of the buck converter that can be calculated using this formula:\nI_{peak} = I_{out} + ((V_{in}-v_{out})*D)/(2*L*freq))\nwhere D is duty cycle: D = V_{out}/V_{in}\nAW32257 maximum charging current is 2.5A @1.5MHz,\nAPW7261 is 1.5A @3MHz,\nTP5100 is 2A @800kHz."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 190.5 78.232 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "57154baa-c5be-425e-b034-a86ec0d017a2")
	)
	(text "R22 sets trickle-charging current to start battery charging slowly,\nwhen the battery voltage is lower then the threshold.\n50K - 20% I, 114K - 30% I, 320K - 50% I, 0 - 100%"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 187.96 161.798 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "69f32d69-79ea-40ce-8944-bbc135b40338")
	)
	(text "R30, R33 and R34 set the current llimit at which battery will be charged.\nOverall value will result in this settings:\n1 Ohm - 100mA, 0.2 - 500mA, 0.1 - 1A, 0.067 - 1.5A, 0.05 - 2A"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 211.582 109.982 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "6e154b3e-4d1c-43c4-89f3-4c863fd897d8")
	)
	(text "Current shunt\n1W"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 158.496 96.012 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "8e5f4901-9b9c-4eba-ba08-f77b468754ea")
	)
	(text "We can use smaller package for D12, because estimated current here\nwill be: I_{D} = (1-duty_cycle)*I_{load}.\nThe worst case scenario: I_{D} = (1-(4.2/12))*2 = 1.3A\nPower dissipation will be 1.3*0,55 = 0,715W\nwhich SOD-123 should handle without any trouble."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 211.836 100.076 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "a6b7aeae-9445-434a-a18a-3a4b0af4666f")
	)
	(text "CS pin is used to select battery voltage\nCS floating - 4.2V or CS high - 8.4V\nCS low - shutdown"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 187.96 154.432 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "cfdc61e5-7291-4960-953d-0bcab1a402cb")
	)
